  "headline": "Redis",
  "description": "Redis is an in-memory data structure store used as a database, cache, message broker, and streaming engine. It supports strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets, bitmaps, hyperloglogs, geospatial indexes, and streams. Sub-millisecond latency, 100K+ ops/sec on modest hardware.",
